The paper deals with optimizing artificial neural networks (ANNs) using neuroevolution, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on addressing the challenges of optimizing high-dimensional ANNs, which suggests that the paper could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions classification tasks, which could indicate a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with control tasks, which could suggest a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
